   "source": [
    "# 27.1 List some ways using which you can reduce underfitting in a model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c924afb9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "What is Underfitting?\n",
    "\n",
    "Underfitting happens when a model is too simple to capture the underlying pattern in data.\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Symptoms:\n",
    "\n",
    "Low training accuracy\n",
    "Low test accuracy\n",
    "High bias\n",
    "✅ Ways to Reduce Underfitting\n",
    "🔹 1. Increase Model Complexity\n",
    "Use a more powerful model\n",
    "Linear → Polynomial\n",
    "Shallow tree → Deep tree\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Helps capture complex patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 2. Add More Features\n",
    "Include relevant variables\n",
    "✔️ Gives model more information\n",
    "🔹 3. Feature Engineering\n",
    "Create meaningful features (interactions, transformations)\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "x\n",
    "2\n",
    ", x\n",
    "3\n",
    ", log(x)\n",
    "🔹 4. Reduce Regularization\n",
    "Lower penalty in:\n",
    "Ridge (L2)\n",
    "Lasso (L1)\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Allows model to fit data better\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 5. Train for Longer (Iterative Models)\n",
    "Increase epochs/iterations\n",
    "✔️ Helps model learn better\n",
    "🔹 6. Use Better Algorithms\n",
    "Switch to more expressive models:\n",
    "Tree-based models\n",
    "Ensemble methods\n",
    "Neural networks\n",
    "🔹 7. Reduce Noise / Improve Data Quality\n",
    "Clean incorrect labels\n",
    "✔️ Helps model learn real patterns\n",
    "🔹 8. Decrease Bias via Ensemble\n",
    "Boosting methods (e.g., Gradient Boosting)\n",
    "✔️ Reduces bias effectively\n",
    "🔹 9. Hyperparameter Tuning\n",
    "Adjust:\n",
    "Depth (trees)\n",
    "Learning rate\n",
    "Number of estimators\n",
    "🎯 Interview-Ready Answer (Short)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Underfitting can be reduced by increasing model complexity, adding relevant features, reducing regularization, training longer, and using more powerful algorithms like ensemble methods.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Pro Tip\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Underfitting is high bias—so we reduce bias by making the model more flexible.”"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "0a768df3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "✅ 1. Overfitting vs Underfitting (Clear Comparison)\n",
    "Aspect\tUnderfitting\tOverfitting\n",
    "Model\tToo simple\tToo complex\n",
    "Bias\tHigh\tLow\n",
    "Variance\tLow\tHigh\n",
    "Training Accuracy\tLow\tVery High\n",
    "Test Accuracy\tLow\tLow\n",
    "Cause\tCan’t learn pattern\tLearns noise\n",
    "Solution\tIncrease complexity\tReduce complexity\n",
    "🎯 Core Concept\n",
    "\n",
    "Total Error=Bias\n",
    "2\n",
    "+Variance+Irreducible Error\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Goal: Balance bias and variance\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ 2. Real Interview Scenarios\n",
    "🔹 Scenario 1: Underfitting\n",
    "Train accuracy = 60%\n",
    "Test accuracy = 58%\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Problem: High Bias (Underfitting)\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ What to say:\n",
    "Increase model complexity\n",
    "Add features\n",
    "Reduce regularization\n",
    "Train longer\n",
    "🔹 Scenario 2: Overfitting\n",
    "Train accuracy = 98%\n",
    "Test accuracy = 72%\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Problem: High Variance (Overfitting)\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ What to say:\n",
    "Apply regularization\n",
    "Reduce complexity\n",
    "Use cross-validation\n",
    "Use ensemble methods\n",
    "🔥 Golden Interview Line\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Gap between train and test → Overfitting; both low → Underfitting.”\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ 3. Quick Revision Cheat Sheet (🔥 Last-Minute Prep)\n",
    "🟢 Reduce Underfitting (High Bias)\n",
    "Increase model complexity\n",
    "Add more features\n",
    "Reduce regularization\n",
    "Train longer\n",
    "Use boosting\n",
    "🔴 Reduce Overfitting (High Variance)\n",
    "Use regularization (L1/L2)\n",
    "Simplify model\n",
    "Feature selection\n",
    "Cross-validation\n",
    "Dropout / pruning\n",
    "Ensemble (bagging)\n",
    "🎯 Final Interview Answer (Perfect)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Underfitting is caused by high bias and can be reduced by increasing model complexity and adding features, while overfitting is caused by high variance and can be reduced using regularization, cross-validation, and simpler models. The goal is to balance bias and variance.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Pro Tip (Use this to stand out)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Always diagnose first using train vs test performance before choosing a solution.”\n",
    "\n",
    "If you want next-level prep, I can give:\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 \n",
    "50 rapid-fire ML interview questions\n",
    "🔥 \n",
    "End-to-end ML system design answers\n",
    "🔥 \n",
    "Mock interview (like real Accenture/KPMG round)"
